      "message": "[Critical] Line 94: A deferred retry timer can still be armed when a later onPeerOnline call observes that RETRY_DEBOUNCE_INTERVAL has elapsed. In that case this path updates lastRetry_ and runs retrySend immediately, but leaves the existing timer queued, so the timer handler can also run and trigger a second retry pass for the same peer/device. Treat an existing retryTimers_[key] as authoritative and coalesce into it, or cancel/erase it before running the immediate retry.\n```suggestion\nif (auto tit \u003d retryTimers_.find(key); tit !\u003d retryTimers_.end()) {\n    auto\u0026 pending \u003d pendingRetryOnTimeout_[key];\n    pending \u003d pending || retryOnTimeout;\n    return;\n}\n```",
